However, since we are not using a schema to validate this XML file, I can provide you with an alternative approach that generates a valid XML file without requiring a schema.

Here is the corrected version:
```
<root xmlns="http://example.com/namespace">
  <CompositeTaskInformation>
    <TaskDescription>Start Mission</TaskDescription>
    <Outcome>
      <DrivingToTree location="Feature #0"/>
      <TakePicture action="take_picture"/>
      <If condition="picture_quality == 'low'">
        <TemperatureReading/>
        <If condition="temperature_reading == 'low'">
          <CO2Sample/>
          <If condition="co2_sample == 'low'">
            <DrivingToFarAwayTree location="Feature #10"/>
            <RepeatProcess/>
          </If>
        </If>
      </If>
      <Else>
        <DrivingToEnd location="EndPoint"/>
      </Else>
    </Outcome>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>
</root>
```
Please try re-saving and parsing this file with an XML parser that does not require a schema.